stairs hallways now set a permanent new baseline elevation

Each room stores its absolute floor height in origin[1]. The stairs
hallway variant rises over the first 6m to a plateau that runs the
remaining 22m at the new altitude - no descent. Every subsequent room
is generated at that raised floor, so the museum gains elevation
permanently as the player climbs more staircases. RoomManager wraps
each (Room, Hallway) pair in a group translated by its floorY so the
interiors can keep using local (floor-relative) y math untouched.

Void-shaft and bridge-of-faces teleport targets now include origin[1]
so the post-cutscene arrival lands on the correct elevated hallway.
